<br>
Here is my &quot;overburn&quot; method.  You should really have SoW tho, so buy em from people or get a 10-pack.  Buy a clarity too, if you want to, although it is not needed.  <br>
<br>
I am specialized Evoc, so this suits me, if you you are Spec Conj you might have better results chain casting pets.<br>
<br>
-Memorize Cinder Bolt and Blaze.<br>
-Keep phantom armor and shielding up.<br>
-Summon Earthpet.   A top pet is best.  Keep Earthpet memmed.<br>
-Buff it with Burnout.   Park pet safe somewhere out of mob paths.<br>
-Drink your SoW.<br>
-Find a HG.   Get at maximum Cinder bolt range.<br>
-Fire 2 or 3 Cinderbolts.   You may have to turn away from<br>
 the target to get enough time to hit the HG with all 3 before he is on<br>
 top of you.  Try to get at least 3 bolts for 1K damage, or<br>
 at least 2 bolts and a Blaze.  HG may be in range to hit you when you get that<br>
 last spell off.  If you can handle the punishment, fine, if not, start <br>
 running earlier.<br>
-Run like hell to pet.   Try and gain some space on the giant.  If you<br>
 get enough space, nuke again with a bolt.<br>
<br>
-Arrive at pet.  By now, you hopefully have done 1K to 1.3K of damage<br>
 to the giant already and the pet is untouched.  Sic pet.  Run in huge <br>
 circle and use f9 view to see when pet root sticks eventually.<br>
<br>
-When root sticks -- Nuke more <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
-Giant dies, 95% of the time if you do this without more then one resist.<br>
<br>
Once you have this down, you seldom lose the fight, and you are SoWed in case things go bad.  Sure, the other methods like chain casting pets, or Nuke/Nuke/heal pet/Nuke/Nuke/Heal Pet also work, but for me they were much less reliable and less safe for HGs.<br>
<br>
Oh, and at 44th, I never met a HG that gave me any trouble.  Earth/Water Pets can nearly solo them.   A damage shield and a nuke was pretty much all they need to die.  Sampox is right about the 49 fire pet tho -- it seems to own HGs the way a cat plays with a mouse. <p><b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
